A Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) Developer is a technical professional who builds, customizes, integrates, and automates solutions in Salesforce Marketing Cloud. While an SFMC Business Analyst or Marketing Automation Specialist focuses on campaign execution and business requirements, an SFMC Developer focuses on the technical implementation.

What does an SFMC Developer do?
1. Develop Email Templates
Build responsive HTML/CSS email templates.
Use AMPscript for dynamic content.
Use Server-Side JavaScript (SSJS) for advanced personalization.
Create reusable content blocks.
2. Write SQL Queries
Create SQL queries in Automation Studio.
Segment audiences.
Populate Data Extensions.
Optimize query performance.
3. Build Automations
Create Automation Studio workflows.
Import/export files.
Schedule SQL activities.
Trigger emails and journeys.
4. Integrate SFMC with Other Systems
Use REST APIs and SOAP APIs.
Integrate with Salesforce CRM.
Connect websites, apps, payment gateways, and third-party systems.
Configure authentication using OAuth.
5. Develop Landing Pages
Create landing pages using CloudPages.
Build forms.
Capture customer information.
Handle form submissions using AMPscript and SSJS.
6. Journey Builder Development
Configure entry sources.
Set decision splits.
Create custom activities.
Implement triggered sends.
7. Data Management
Design Data Extensions.
Create Contact Builder relationships.
Manage synchronized data sources.
Ensure data quality.
8. Personalization
Dynamic email content.
Personalized subject lines.
Conditional content.
Product recommendations.
9. Debugging
Resolve automation failures.
Troubleshoot API errors.
Fix AMPscript issues.
Optimize SQL queries.
